<p>i am trying to get the child (simple) item from his parent (configurable) with an order_item in Magento.</p>  <pre><code>    $item = Mage::getModel('sales/order_item')-&gt;load($itemId);     if ($item-&gt;getproduct_type() == 'configurable'){         $children = $item-&gt;getChildrenItems();         var_dump(count($children));     } </code></pre>  <p>here my item is well loaded as i am able to display my var_dump, but the count is always to 0. I tried with getChildrenItems and getChildren, both are not giving me the child. However, when i look in my database, I have a simple product with my parent_item_id given in this order.</p>  <p>Thanks</p>  <p>Edit : </p>  <p>i did a quick fix going backwards to the order and parsing the whole order, but it seems dirty to me so I d like to understand why getChildrenItems is not working.</p>  <p>My fix is :</p>  <pre><code>$item = Mage::getModel('sales/order_item')-&gt;load($itemId);     if ($item-&gt;getproduct_type() == 'configurable'){         $order = Mage::getModel('sales/order')-&gt;load($item-&gt;getorder_id());         if ($order != null){             foreach ($order-&gt;getAllItems() as $i){                 if ($i-&gt;getparent_item_id() == $itemId){                     //doing stuff here                     $i-&gt;save();                  }             }         }     } </code></pre>